DESCRIPTION: With all modules connected and all switches ON, measure the voltage between the two cables on the INPUT side of control module 6 (coming from module 5) and then between the two cables on its OUTPUT side (going to module 7). Determine at which side of control module 6 the 12 V disappears and whether polarity remains correct.,
RESULT: The 12 V is present on the INPUT side of control module 6 (Control Input Cable (+) 6 at about 11.99 V relative to ground), and absent on the OUTPUT side (both Control Output Cables (+) 6 and (−) 6 at 0 V). No POLARITY INVERSION DETECTED: the (+) input is at +12 V and the (−) input is at 0 V, while both output cables are at 0 V.
Current persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:
No circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.


